HEADWORD: Boston
<hw>Bos"ton</hw> <pr>(<?/)</pr>, <pos>n.</pos> <def>A game at cards,
played by four persons, with two packs of fifty-two cards each; -- said
to be so called from <etsep>Boston,</etsep> Massachusetts, and to have
been invented by officers of the French army in America during the
Revolutionary war.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

